Run 10 Feed 10, an initiative backed by Unilever, Women’s Health magazine, the Feed Foundation and others, will use 10-kilometer races to generate donations of food to the poor.














Advertising

                    A Backstage Pass to a High-End Food Festival                
Nearly two dozen videos from the Food & Wine Classic in Aspen will be shown online, in part underscoring the mayonnaise maker Hellmann’s pledge to switch to cage-free eggs by 2020.










Advertising

                    Clear Hair Products Enter a Cluttered Market                
Unilever brings Clear, a hair-care brand already sold in 42 countries, to the United States with a different formulation and diverse marketing.










ADVERTISING

                    Clear Hair Products Enter a Cluttered Market                
WHITE RAIN. Halo.Breck. Drene. Prell. Agree. Hälsa. Lustre-Creme. Gee, Your Hair Smells Terrific. Vidal Sassoon. Flex. There are enough discontinued, forgotten, moribund or also-ran hair-care brands to make marketers want to, well, pull out their hair. But that is not deterring Unilever, the consumer products giant. Unilever, which sells hair-care products under names like Dove, Finesse, Nexxus, Suave, TRESemmé and VO5, is introducing another hair-care brand in the United States.










Advertising

                    Mixing Marketing With Social Games and Extreme Sports                
Degree Men, the deodorant by Unilever, is trying to increase the interaction with 18- to 35-year-old consumers with content that is tailored to social gaming sites.










ADVERTISING

                    Mixing Marketing With Social Games and Extreme Sports                
DEGREE MEN, the deodorant by Unilever, is starting a video marketing campaign that aims to increase the brand's interaction with its core consumers by offering content tailored to social gaming sites. The brand is joining companies like Coca-Cola, Disney and Pinnacle Foods' Aunt Jemima Frozen Breakfast in trying what has become known as engagement marketing. Degree Men's video series, ''Masters of Movement,'' features extreme-sports figures and allows social game players who view their two-minute videos to earn points and currency that can be used in the game they are playing.










Advertising

                    Axe Adds Fragrance for Women to Its Lineup                
Axe, the Unilever brand, has so far been pitched at young men, with ads depicting women smelling Axe users and aggressively pursuing them.










DealBook

                    Mrs. Dash Finds a Home at B&G Foods                
B&G Foods loves Mrs. Dash.










Business Briefing | Company News

                    Unilever Buys Russian Cosmetics Brand                
The Anglo-Dutch firm has agreed to buy an 82 percent stake in Concern Kalina, a Russian cosmetics brand, for $537 million.










DealBook

                    Unilever Buys Russian Cosmetics Brand                
With Western economies struggling to avoid a double-dip recession, European consumer product's giant Unilever is heading East.










Campaign Spotlight

                    Unilever Tries to Corner ‘Stock’ Market                
Knorr, a giant food brand owned by Unilever, pulls out the stops to introduce a new concentrated stock broth globally.










