Unilever N.V. Key Developments

Unilever N.V. Announces Unaudited Earnings Results for the First Half Ended June 30, 2017 and Unaudited Turnover Results for the Second Quarter Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 20 17
Unilever N.V. announced unaudited earnings results for the first half ended June 30, 2017 and unaudited turnover results for the second quarter ended June 30, 2017. For the period, the company reported turnover of EUR 27,725 million compared to EUR 26,283 million a year ago. Operating profit was EUR 4,847 million compared to EUR 3,789 million a year ago. Profit before taxation was EUR 4,632 million compared to EUR 3,638 million a year ago. Net profit was EUR 2,710 million compared to EUR 2,658 million a year ago. Net profit attributable to shareholders' equity was EUR 3,110 million compared to EUR 2,512 million a year ago. Diluted earnings per share were EUR 1.09 compared to basic and diluted earnings per share of EUR 0.88 a year ago. Underlying profit attributable to shareholders’ equity was EUR 3,206 million or EUR 1.13 per diluted share against EUR 2,812 million or EUR 0.99 per diluted share a year ago. Net cash flow from operating activities was EUR 2,185 million compared to EUR 1,819 million a year ago. Net capital expenditure was EUR 672 million compared to EUR 759 million a year ago. Closing net debt was EUR 13.8 billion compared with EUR 12.6 billion as at 31 December 2016, mainly reflecting the share buy-backs of EUR 1.4 billion the company have undertaken so far in May and June 2017.

For the second quarter of 2017, the company reported turnover of EUR 14.4 billion, an increase of 4.9% from 2016.


Unilever N.V. Announces Interim Dividend for Second Quarter of 2017, Payable on September 6, 2017
Jul 20 17
Unilever N.V. announced interim dividend of €0.3585 per ordinary share for second quarter of 2017. The dividend is payable on September 6, 2017 to holders of record at the close of business on 4 August 2017. The ex-dividend date is August 3, 2017.


Unilever Competes with Hormel to buy £2.2 bn Reckitt Benckiser food unit
Jul 17 17
Unilever N.V. (ENXTAM:UNA) and Hormel Foods Corporation (NYSE:HRL) are reportedly seeking to buy the foods division of Reckitt Benckiser Group plc (LSE:RB.), the Sunday Times newspaper reported, citing sources. Unilever and Hormel are front-runners in a deal that is likely to top £2.2 billion ($2.9 billion), the unidentified sources told the Sunday Times.


