Management
 What is the CEO of Unilever N.V's salary, the management and board of directors tenure and is there insider trading?

Management is one of the most important areas of a company. We look at unreasonable CEO compensation, how long the team and board of directors have been around for and insider trading.



CEO








Paul Polman

COMPENSATION€7,697,000
AGE60




CEO Bio

Mr. Paulus Gerardus Josephus Maria Polman, also known as Paul, has been Chief Executive Officer and Executive Director of Unilever South Africa (Pty) Ltd since January 1, 2009 and October 2008 respectively. Mr. Polman has been the Chief Executive Officer of The Unilever Group, Unilever NV and Unilever Plc since January 1, 2009. Mr. Polman serves as Chief Executive Officer at Unilever Vietnam International Company Limited. He served as the President of Kilimanjaro Blind trust. He served as the Chief Financial Officer of Nestlé S.A. from January 01, 2006 to 2008 and also served as its Member of Executive Board, Head of North & South American Business and Executive Vice President of Finance Control, Legal, Tax and Purchasing & Export. He served as an Executive Vice President of Nestle where he was responsible for leading the Americas businesses since February 2008. Mr. Polman served as Group President of Western Europe of Procter & Gamble Co. from July 1, 2004 to June 2005 and served as its President of Western Europe until June 2004. He served as a Group President of Procter & Gamble's European business from 2001 to 2005. He served as President of Global Fabric Care at P&G from 1998 to 2001; Vice President and Managing Director, P&G UK from 1995 to 1998; Vice President and General Manager, P&G Iberia from 1989 to 1995 and Category Manager and Marketing Director of Baby, FemPro, Cleanser and Beverages, P&G France from 1986 to 1989. He served various assignments of increasing responsibility in Finance in Belgium, Holland and France leading to Associate Finance position from 1979 to 1986. Mr. Polman began his career in 1979 with Procter & Gamble in finance and acquired a broad executive experience through assignments in Belgium, Holland, France, Spain, the United Kingdom and the United States. Mr. Polman serves as Chairman of the Board of Directors of Enterprises Maggi S.A., Nestlé Finance S.A., Nestlé International Travel Retail S.A., Nestlé Capital Advisers and Intercona Re AG. He serves as Chairman of Perkins International Advisory Board. He has been an Executive Director of Unilever plc since October 2008. He serves as a Member of The Board of Directors at United Nations Global Compact. He has been a Director of The Dow Chemical Company since February 11, 2010. He has been an Executive Director of Unilever NV since October 2008. He serves as a Director of Life Ventures S.A., Nutrition-Wellness Venture AG, Unilac, Inc. (Panama) and Food Products (Holdings) (Panama). He served as a Director of Alcon Inc. from May 2, 2006 to September 2008. He serves as a Member of Global Advisory Council at Acumen Fund, Inc. He serves as Vice Chairman of the European Round Table, a member of the International Business Council of the World Economic Forum, the Swiss American Chamber of Commerce and a Director of Conservation International. He serves as Chairman of Executive Committee at World Business Council for Sustainable Development, Geneva. He is a Trustee of both the Leverhulme Trust and Asia House. He is on the Board of the Consumer Goods Forum where he co-chairs the Board Strategy and the Sustainability Committees. Mr. Polman received a B.B.A and B.A from the University of Groningen, Netherlands in 1977, M.A. Economics from University of Cincinnati, USA in 1979, M.B.A. Finance/International Marketing from University of Cincinnati, USA in 1979 and a Doctor of Civil Law from University of Northumbria at Newcastle, UK (Honorary Degree) in 2000.


CEO Compensation 

CEO's compensation has been consistent with company performance over the past year.

CEO's compensation appears reasonable.



